<h2>How GST works on AI subscriptions</h2>

<p>Since OIDAR (Online Information Database Access and Retrieval) rules came into effect in India:</p>

<ul>
  <li>All foreign SaaS providers selling to Indian users must charge 18% GST</li>
  <li>The 18% is added to the displayed price at checkout (some tools display inclusive, some exclusive, check carefully)</li>
  <li>If you have a GSTIN, you can claim this as input credit, if you add your GSTIN to billing</li>
  <li>Without a GSTIN, you pay the 18% but can't claim it back</li>
</ul>

<p>For business users, getting a GSTIN often pays for itself in claimed input credit on AI tool subscriptions alone.</p>

