<h2>Frequently asked pricing questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Why is the price higher than what the tool's website shows?</h3>
  <p>The website typically shows pre-GST pricing in USD. After conversion to INR + 18% GST + 1-3.5% bank forex markup, your actual charge is ~22-25% higher than the listed price.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Are AI tool subscriptions tax-deductible for Indian businesses?</h3>
  <p>Yes, if used for business. Save the invoices. The full subscription is a deductible business expense for income tax. The 18% GST is claimable as input credit if you're GST-registered.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>What's the cheapest way to access multiple AI tools?</h3>
  <p>Use free tiers strategically: Claude free + ChatGPT free + Gemini free covers 90% of casual use. Add one paid tool, whichever you'll actually use daily. Most "AI tool stacks" you see online are over-engineered for basic users.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Can I get an Indian-priced subscription instead of USD?</h3>
  <p>Generally no for foreign SaaS. Some tools have country-specific pricing but most don't. Indian-built tools (Sarvam, Krutrim, Cleartax) bill in INR by default.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>How do I avoid forex markup?</h3>
  <p>Use a forex card (Niyo Global, HDFC Forex Plus, IDFC FIRST). They charge a flat ₹0 - 250 issuance fee but no per-transaction forex markup. Saves 1-3.5% on every payment.</p>
</div>

<h2>Final pricing reality check</h2>

<p>Most Indian users overspend on AI tools by 50-200%. The pattern: subscribing to 4-5 tools because of FOMO, using only 1-2 actively. Audit your subscriptions every quarter. If you haven't opened a tool in 30 days, cancel.</p>

<p>The right Indian AI stack costs ₹500-2,500/month, not ₹10,000+. Start small, scale only when usage justifies it.</p>

